From 82023fe91c25ac471c5572bcf118b28f8819a16e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rudraksh sisodia <rudrakshsisodia@Rudrakshs-MacBook-Pro.local>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 14:20:45 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] feat(checkpoint): event log, checkpoints, side-effect ledger
 (P2 core)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds pkg/checkpoint (issues #36/#37 core, in-process):
- Snapshotter interface + content-hashed LocalSnapshotter (object-store
  backend is a drop-in behind the same interface later)
- Service: per-job monotonic event log; checkpoint Write/Latest/Restore
- Ledger: Check/Commit/Do — replay-safe, exactly-once external effects

Hardens the P1 store it builds on:
- store_test.go: outbox txn, conditional status transition, per-org
  idempotency, side-effect ledger, additive cost
- fix GORM composite unique tags to match migration 0001:
  (org_id,idempotency_key), (job_id,seq), (job_id,event_seq),
  (org_id,name,version) were each collapsed to a single-column global
  unique, diverging from the SQL migration under AutoMigrate

Tests: snapshot round-trip (identical hash), monotonic seq, checkpoint
restore, ledger fires once, and crash -> restore -> replay converges
with zero double-fired effects.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
